{
  "$comment": [
    "Canonical strings the skills must emit and the evaluators must match.",
    "Universal and Codex SKILL.md stay self-contained; a packaged plugin may ship a pinned references/ runtime dependency.",
    "Canonical strings still live in every skill copy — this file is the authority they are",
    "checked against, mechanically, by scripts/check-format.py at release and in CI.",
    "Edit a string here and in every file listed under `files`, or the check fails.",
    "fenced_must_contain: the one block that actually gets copied. A rule can be word-perfect in the prose and absent from the template, and then nobody ever emits it.",
    "required_verbatim strings require presence anywhere; {literal, selector, count} pins load-bearing text to a structural section/fence and exact cardinality. This is the deliberately narrow parity mechanism for the hand-maintained <plugin>/ copy."
  ],
  "forbidden_everywhere": {
    "$comment": "A removed behavior leaves no notice behind: the spec reads as if it never existed. Scanned across markdown AND the shipped yaml/json entry shells — residue in an entry shell ships just the same.",
    "patterns": [
      "jsdelivr",
      "agency-agents@main",
      "four-tier",
      "四层",
      "fetched tier",
      "ADVISORY-CERTIFIED",
      "ADVISORY CERTIFIED",
      "ADVISORY_CERTIFIED"
    ],
    "$regex_comment": "越权搭配是一类不是三个拼写：大写 ADVISORY token 后 30 字内跟 certif/audit PASS/audited（30 抓得住剥完 unaudited 后正规 token 尾随的越权≈22 字，又放过 Terms 里 token 定义的合法解释≈37 字）；certif*（任意大小写，含全大写 CERTIFIED）前置 40 字内；audited/audit PASS 前置 20 字内。扫描前剥掉 non-certif*/unaudited。窗口值都是对全部扫描根实测过零误伤的。",
    "regex_patterns": [
      "ADVISORY[^\\n]{0,30}(?i:certif|audit PASS|audited)",
      "(?i:certif\\w*)[^\\n]{0,40}ADVISORY",
      "(?i:audit PASS|audited)[^\\n]{0,20}ADVISORY"
    ],
    "files": [
      "skills",
      "review-loop",
      "council",
      "opsx",
      "codex-plugins",
      "README.md",
      ".claude-plugin",
      ".agents"
    ]
  },
  "skills": {
    "review-loop": {
      "files": [
        "skills/review-loop/SKILL.md",
        "review-loop/skills/review-loop/SKILL.md",
        "codex-plugins/review-loop/skills/review-loop/SKILL.md"
      ],
      "tiers": [
        "registered",
        "local"
      ],
      "marker_prefix": null,
      "$comment_prefix": "Evaluator ⑦ matches this literal. It MUST be a prefix of every marker form below — that is the check that catches a stray backtick or a renamed marker silently disarming the cap.",
      "marker_forms": [],
      "required_verbatim": [
        "A CR APPROVE without its deliverable is not a pass",
        "CAPPED (catalog self-installed)",
        "[local: <catalog path>]",
        "not-run(tier unverified)"
      ],
      "catalog_paths": {
        "Code Reviewer": "engineering/engineering-code-reviewer.md",
        "Reality Checker": "testing/testing-reality-checker.md",
        "Minimal Change Engineer": "engineering/engineering-minimal-change-engineer.md",
        "Application Security Engineer": "security/security-appsec-engineer.md",
        "Backend Architect": "engineering/engineering-backend-architect.md",
        "Backend Architect (mcp-memory variant)": "integrations/mcp-memory/backend-architect-with-memory.md",
        "Blockchain Security Auditor": "security/security-blockchain-security-auditor.md"
      },
      "echo_labels": [
        "Slots:",
        "Augment:",
        "Scope fence:",
        "Anchors:",
        "Simplicity:",
        "Legibility:"
      ],
      "tokens": [
        "APPROVE",
        "CHANGES-REQUESTED",
        "CLEAR",
        "APPROVE-DEGRADED",
        "CAPPED",
        "OUT-OF-SCOPE-PENDING"
      ],
      "$comment_echo": "The status block is what the evaluator reads. A renamed label is a predicate that silently stops firing.",
      "exhaustive": [],
      "fenced_must_contain": [
        "[local: testing/testing-reality-checker.md]"
      ]
    },
    "openspec-apply-change-subagent": {
      "files": [
        "skills/openspec-apply-change-subagent/SKILL.md",
        "opsx/skills/openspec-apply-change-subagent/SKILL.md",
        "codex-plugins/opsx/skills/openspec-apply-change-subagent/SKILL.md"
      ],
      "tiers": [
        "registered",
        "local"
      ],
      "marker_prefix": null,
      "marker_forms": [],
      "required_verbatim": [
        "<组>/<角色>：[local: <源路径>]"
      ],
      "catalog_paths": {
        "Frontend Developer": "engineering/engineering-frontend-developer.md",
        "Backend Architect": "engineering/engineering-backend-architect.md",
        "Data Engineer": "engineering/engineering-data-engineer.md",
        "Database Optimizer": "engineering/engineering-database-optimizer.md",
        "DevOps Automator": "engineering/engineering-devops-automator.md",
        "Minimal Change Engineer": "engineering/engineering-minimal-change-engineer.md"
      },
      "echo_labels": [
        "<组>/<角色>：[local:"
      ],
      "tokens": [],
      "$comment_echo": "The tier echo is keyed per expert: the 数据 group can dispatch two, and two identical markers hide a dropped one.",
      "exhaustive": [],
      "fenced_must_contain": [
        "[local: engineering/engineering-frontend-developer.md]"
      ]
    },
    "council": {
      "files": [
        "skills/council/SKILL.md",
        "council/skills/council/SKILL.md",
        "codex-plugins/council/skills/council/SKILL.md"
      ],
      "tiers": [
        "synthesized"
      ],
      "marker_prefix": null,
      "marker_forms": [],
      "required_verbatim": [
        {"literal": "find ~/.agency-agents -mindepth 2 -type f -name '*.md' \\\n  ! -iname 'README*' ! -iname 'CONTRIBUTING*' ! -iname 'SECURITY.md' ! -path '*/.github/*' 2>/dev/null | sort", "selector": "section-prefix:1.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "candidate-digest: sha256:<digest>", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "retry-for: <failed k>", "selector": "section-prefix:2.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "re-dispatch-for: <superseded k>", "selector": "section-prefix:2.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "post-confirmation-attestation", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "post-candidate evidence envelope", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 2},
        {"literal": "predate the first seat dispatch", "selector": "section-prefix:6.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "platform-authored confirmation record", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "confirmation-provenance", "selector": "before-section-prefix:0.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "audited only: audit-procedure:", "selector": "fences-in-section-prefix:0.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "version/commit:<id>", "selector": "fences-in-section-prefix:0.", "count": 2},
        {"literal": "full SHA-256", "selector": "section-prefix:1.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "git status --porcelain=v1 -z -uall", "selector": "before-section-prefix:0.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "settle/re-read", "selector": "before-section-prefix:0.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "Reserve the line prefixes", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "any such line in candidate bytes is A9 failure", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "if candidate bytes must change, build and freeze `candidate-<n+1>.md` with a fresh audit budget", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "**`ADVISORY (debate-converged; unaudited)`**", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "**`ADVISORY (N open; unaudited)`**", "selector": "section-prefix:5.", "count": 1},
        {"literal": "must never cite agreement as support", "selector": "before-section-prefix:0.", "count": 1}
      ],
      "catalog_paths": {
        "Backend Architect": "engineering/engineering-backend-architect.md",
        "Backend Architect (mcp-memory variant)": "integrations/mcp-memory/backend-architect-with-memory.md"
      },
      "echo_labels": [
        "opposing:"
      ],
      "tokens": [
        "CONVERGED",
        "ADVISORY",
        "UNRESOLVED",
        "STOPPED"
      ],
      "$comment_echo": "The auditor parses the seat echo literally (A2). A drifted format is an audit that cannot reconcile.",
      "exhaustive": [],
      "fenced_must_contain": [
        "-> seated",
        "synthesized"
      ]
    }
  },
  "consumer_surfaces": {
    "$comment": "Installation-facing council descriptions must expose both assurance tiers and the advisory authority boundary.",
    "council": {
      "targets": [
        {
          "file": ".claude-plugin/marketplace.json",
          "selector": "json:plugins[name=council].description"
        },
        {
          "file": "council/.claude-plugin/plugin.json",
          "selector": "json:description"
        },
        {
          "file": "codex-plugins/council/.codex-plugin/plugin.json",
          "selector": "json:description"
        },
        {
          "file": "codex-plugins/council/.codex-plugin/plugin.json",
          "selector": "json:interface.shortDescription"
        },
        {
          "file": "codex-plugins/council/.codex-plugin/plugin.json",
          "selector": "json:interface.longDescription"
        },
        {
          "file": "codex-plugins/council/skills/council/agents/openai.yaml",
          "selector": "line:short_description"
        },
        {
          "file": "README.md",
          "selector": "section:收录的 skill"
        },
        {
          "file": "skills/council/SKILL.md",
          "selector": "line:description"
        },
        {
          "file": "council/skills/council/SKILL.md",
          "selector": "line:description"
        },
        {
          "file": "codex-plugins/council/skills/council/SKILL.md",
          "selector": "line:description"
        }
      ],
      "required": [
        "ADVISORY",
        "CONVERGED",
        "non-authorizing"
      ]
    }
  },
  "catalog": {
    "$comment": "Checked against a real checkout when one is present at ~/.agency-agents; skipped with a notice otherwise. This is what proves the path table is not fiction — the flaw that let `Application Security Engineer` resolve to nothing on a clean install.",
    "repo": "https://github.com/msitarzewski/agency-agents",
    "min_depth": 2
  },
  "families": [
    {
      "$comment": "Applied to every checked file, not per-skill: a family is only closed where nobody forgot it.",
      "regex": "CAPPED\\s*\\([^)]*\\)",
      "allowed": [
        "CAPPED (cap-reached, N items left)",
        "CAPPED (catalog self-installed)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "regex": "not-run\\([^)]*\\)",
      "allowed": [
        "not-run(...)",
        "not-run(content-filter)",
        "not-run(empty)",
        "not-run(missing guard checklist)",
        "not-run(tier unverified)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "regex": "APPROVE-DEGRADED \\([^)]*\\)",
      "allowed": [
        "APPROVE-DEGRADED (<all reasons, one parenthesis>)",
        "APPROVE-DEGRADED (bloat: +N over 2 rounds, no lane removed anything)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "$comment": "ADVISORY is a terminal debate result, never an audit or implementation authorization.",
      "regex": "(?m)^[ \\t]*(?:\\|[^|\\r\\n]*\\|[ \\t]*\\*\\*`)?(?P<token>ADVISORY[^\\r\\n`*|]*)",
      "allowed": [
        "ADVISORY (N open; unaudited)",
        "ADVISORY (debate-converged; unaudited)",
        "ADVISORY (…)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "regex": "STOPPED \\([^)]*\\)",
      "allowed": [
        "STOPPED (advisory is analysis-only)",
        "STOPPED (advisory side effect detected)",
        "STOPPED (awaiting human)",
        "STOPPED (cannot run expert seats)",
        "STOPPED (no real experts: a second axis has no match)",
        "STOPPED (no real experts: catalog unavailable)",
        "STOPPED (no real experts: none on the opposing axis)",
        "STOPPED (not a council question)",
        "STOPPED (proposition needs splitting)",
        "STOPPED (seats exhausted)",
        "STOPPED (…)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "$comment": "Evaluator ⑫ matches these literally. A stray capital or backtick here disarms the check that a claimed strongest-tier expert was ever dispatched.",
      "regex": "\\[\\s*[Rr]egistered[^\\]\\n]*\\]",
      "allowed": [
        "[registered]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "regex": "\\[\\s*[Ll]ocal[^\\]\\n]*\\]",
      "allowed": [
        "[local: <catalog path>]",
        "[local: <path>]",
        "[local: <源路径>]",
        "[local: engineering/engineering-frontend-developer.md]",
        "[local: security/security-blockchain-security-auditor.md]",
        "[local: testing/testing-reality-checker.md]"
      ],
      "$comment": "A pathless local marker is the cheapest lie the ladder names; it is not a legal form."
    },
    {
      "$comment": "The prerequisite halt is a hand-back, not a verdict; one canonical form.",
      "regex": "PREREQUISITE-MISSING\\s*\\([^)]*\\)",
      "allowed": [
        "PREREQUISITE-MISSING (<lane> — see README)"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
